Package: MixviR
Title: Explore DNA/Amino Acid Variation and Infer Lineages in Mixed Genomic Microbial Samples Including SARS-CoV-2
Version: 3.3.3.0000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Michael", "Sovic", role = c("aut", "ccp", "cre"), email = "sovic.1@osu.edu", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8556-3704")),
    person("Francesca", "Savona", role = c("res")),
    person("Zuzana", "Bohrerova", role = c("res", "fnd")),  
    person("Seth", "Faith", role = c("ccp", "ctb"), comment = c(ORDIC = "0000-0002-0441-9859")))
Author: Michael Sovic <sovic.1@osu.edu>
Maintainer: Michael Sovic <sovic.1@osu.edu>
Description: Explore DNA and amino acid variation and infer presence of specific lineages in short-read DNA sequence samples from a target group that potentially contain mixtures of variants/lineages. Originally created to help analyze environmental SARS-CoV-2 (Covid-19) samples from environmental sources such as wastewater or dust, but can be applied to any microbial group.
